[
    {
        "content": "<p>It depends on additional hypotheses on the factorization system (see for example \"algebraic factorization system\"). Often <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> will be universal in some way (so <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span> might be a kernel/cokernel, say).</p>",
        "id": 402014313,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1699976890
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's always a reflection from the slice category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{C}/c&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0019em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> into the subcategory <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{M}/c&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0019em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>...</p>",
        "id": 402028969,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1699981128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Assuming by \"factorization system\" you mean an \"orthogonal/unique\" factorization system.)</p>",
        "id": 402029038,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1699981149
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sometimes <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span> is a pullback, and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> arises as the induced map into it; google \"simple factorization system\", and in particular a paper from Cassidy, Hebert and Kelly. Or read my PhD thesis, which is an account of torsion theories (particularly well-behaved FS, covered in non-abelian setting also in Borceux, handbook tome 1) in triangulated/stable-homotopic setting.</p>",
        "id": 402059957,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1699992178
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As Morgan says, AFS are another source of factorization obtained from universal properties; Garner's paper is the best reading.</p>\n<p>In general, very little can be said, without knowing what are the specifics of the FS you have to handle. For example, is it right proper (=every <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> is a monic)? Extremal-right proper (=every <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> is an extremal monic)?</p>",
        "id": 402060248,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1699992284
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276777\">Mike Shulman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/universal.20property.20of.20images/near/402029038\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(Assuming by \"factorization system\" you mean an \"orthogonal/unique\" factorization system.)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah I do!</p>",
        "id": 402157949,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1700031217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276777\">Mike Shulman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/universal.20property.20of.20images/near/402028969\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It's always a reflection from the slice category $\\mathcal{C}/c'$ into the subcategory $\\mathcal{M}/c'$...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This sounds like what I need! Thanks Mike</p>",
